Bank OZK (Bank of the Ozarks) Logo Bank OZK is a regional bank headquartered in Little Rock, Arkansas with more than 250 locations in ten states: Arkansas, Georgia, Florida, Texas, North Carolina, South Carolina, California, New York and Mississippi and $23.55 billion in assets as of December 31, 2019. Bank OZK is currently concentrated in the southeastern U.S., with 25 or more branches in four states: Arkansas, Georgia, Florida, and North Carolina. Source

Old National Bank Logo
Old National Bank is an American regional bank with nearly 200 retail branches operated by Old National Bancorp and based in Evansville, Indiana. With assets at $20.9 billion and 185 banking centers, Old National Bancorp is the largest financial services bank holding company headquartered in Indiana and one of the top 100 banking companies in the U.S. Its primary banking footprint is in Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, Minnesota, and Wisconsin.
